# Pull Request Quality Standards

## PR Description Requirements

Every pull request must include these sections:

### Summary
One paragraph explaining what changed and why. Link to the issue or ticket.

### Changes
A categorized list of what was modified:

| Category | Files | Key Change |
|----------|-------|------------|
| source | `src/auth.ts` | Added OAuth2 PKCE flow |
| test | `tests/auth.test.ts` | Covers token refresh edge case |
| config | `.env.example` | New `OAUTH_CLIENT_ID` variable |

### Testing
How was this tested? Include:
- Which tests were added or modified
- Manual testing steps performed
- Commands to verify (`mvn test`, `npm test`)

### Risks and Rollback
- Is this a breaking change? Yes / No
- Risk level: Low / Medium / High -- explain why
- Rollback plan: "Revert this commit" or specific steps

## Size Limits

| PR Size | Lines Changed | Guidance |
|---------|---------------|----------|
| Small | < 200 | Ideal. Easy to review. |
| Medium | 200 - 500 | Acceptable. Provide good description. |
| Large | 500 - 1000 | Consider splitting. Justify in description. |
| Too large | > 1000 | Must split unless migration/generated code. |

### Splitting Large PRs

When a PR exceeds 500 lines:

1. Split by feature area or layer (API, service, data)
2. Split into preparatory refactoring + feature
3. Use stacked PRs with clear dependency notes
4. Mark generated or boilerplate code explicitly

## Self-Review Checklist (Before Requesting Review)

Before requesting review, the author must verify:

- [ ] PR title follows conventional format: `type(scope): description`
- [ ] Description is complete (summary, changes, testing, risks)
- [ ] All CI checks pass
- [ ] No unresolved merge conflicts
- [ ] No debug statements, commented-out code, or TODOs left in
- [ ] No secrets or credentials in the diff
- [ ] Tests are included for new behavior
- [ ] Documentation is updated if public API changed
- [ ] Branch is up to date with `main`
- [ ] I have reviewed the diff myself before requesting others

## Review Turnaround

- First review within 1 business day
- Author responds to feedback within 1 business day
- Blocking issues must be resolved before merge
- Do not merge your own PR without at least 1 approval (except trivial docs/typo fixes)

## Draft PRs

Use draft PRs for:
- Work in progress that needs early feedback
- Changes that depend on another PR
- Spike or prototype work

Convert to ready-for-review only when CI passes and self-review checklist is complete.

## PR Labels

Apply labels to aid triage:

| Label | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `breaking-change` | Contains breaking changes |
| `needs-review` | Ready for review |
| `needs-docs` | Documentation update required |
| `hotfix` | Urgent production fix |
| `do-not-merge` | Blocked or waiting on dependency |
